# PTOwl API — manual test calls via the VS Code REST Client extension
# (humao.rest-client, recommended in .vscode/extensions.json).
#
# Usage:
#   1. Open this file in VS Code with the REST Client extension installed.
#   2. Click "Send Request" above any `###` block.
#   3. Response opens in a side pane with status, headers, and body.
#
# Switch between prod and local by commenting/uncommenting @base below.

@base = https://ptowl.com
# @base = http://localhost:8787

### Health check — no auth required, useful for smoke tests
GET {{base}}/api/v1/health

### Clerk environment fingerprint — confirms ClerkProvider URLs + auth strategies
# Useful for debugging when the dashboard says one thing and code says another.
GET https://clerk.ptowl.com/v1/environment

### Auth me — requires a real Clerk session cookie
# To get one: sign in via the browser, open DevTools > Application >
# Cookies > ptowl.com, copy the __session value.
GET {{base}}/api/v1/auth/me
Cookie: __session=<paste-session-jwt-here>

### List my schedules
GET {{base}}/api/v1/schedules
Cookie: __session=<paste-session-jwt-here>

### List my templates
GET {{base}}/api/v1/templates
Cookie: __session=<paste-session-jwt-here>

### Admin decide (magic-link target — JWT in URL, no cookie needed)
# The token comes from the founder's approval email. Use ?decision=approve
# or ?decision=deny. After-image: GET /api/v1/auth/me as that user to
# confirm the status flip.
GET {{base}}/admin/decide?token=<paste-jwt>&decision=approve

### Patient share view (public, no auth) — replace token with a real one
GET {{base}}/p/0000000000000000000000000000ffff
